Serverless Contact Form using AWS

Project Overview

This project demonstrates how to build a serverless contact form using AWS services. The form collects user information such as name, email, and message and stores it in a cloud database without managing any servers.

The project uses the following AWS services:

Amazon API Gateway – Creates an API endpoint for the form
AWS Lambda – Processes the form request
Amazon DynamoDB – Stores the contact form data

The frontend is built using HTML and JavaScript.

Architecture

The workflow of the application is as follows:

User submits the form from the browser.

HTML Contact Form
↓
API Gateway (POST /contact)
↓
AWS Lambda Function
↓
DynamoDB Table (Stores name, email, message)

